name: Odd Tales Book 6 -Nokee the Genocidal Dolphin
description:
The sixth Odd Tales book and the only one not included in the "Odd Tales" Hardcover. I originally printed these as an exclusive for the 2013 NYCC. To my surprise they sold out on the first day.
Re-edited and reprinted, this is the story of Nokee, a dolphin who hates tuna end decides to rid the sea of them.
24 pages of badly drawn and hastily written drivel that is sure to keep you entertained for minutes.

name: Odd Tales Hardcover
description:
Steve Vincent's Hardcover "Odd Tales" anthology. Collects all 5 "Odd Tales" books in a nice 164 page hardcover.
Every book ordered for here comes signed.

Includes all Odd Tales books from 1996-2012
Devilboy in the Land of Love
The Boy who ate the World
Old Woman in the Shoe (revisited)
The Snow Prince
The Stopping of Harold
and all the mini books

A collection of Odd Tales and Macabre cartoons from underground comic book author Steven Vincent. Most of these are reprinted from Steven Vincents first book Devilboy in the Land of Love. This is perfect for the kids in your class who listened to a lot of Joy Division growing up and who now have kids of their own to traumatize. Simple looking, but pleasantly diverting. Not for those without a sense of humor. -Marc Mason-Movie PoopShoot

 This is Edward Gorey and Shel Silverstenin after they finish off a handle of Jack and double team Mother Goose. -Lollipop Magazine

 A collection of 20 stories, which tend to either be a standard comic book type arrangements (panels, silly sound effects, dialogue balloons, etc) or illustrated, humorous verse. The later style shows off Vincent's clever use of rhyme and makes the best use of his drawing style-I forgot
